    <b>Do you have what it takes?</b></font><br>
    <font size=1><b>Date:</b> Sunday, February 23 @ 12:07:40 CET<br><b>Topic:</b> News</font><br><br>
    </center>
    <font size="2">
    <b><h1><center>Remedy cross server recruitment now open</center></h2></b><br><br><center><b><h3>Do you have what it takes to kill with these bad boys?</h3></b>

<br><br>

<img src=http://www.amm-electronics.net/remedy/kickass.JPG></center>

<br><br>

Tired of going nowhere on your current server? All the big guilds are on American or Asian timezone, and you can't stand raiding all night anymore? Want to experience the high end game? Remedy is now accepting cross server recruits again.

<br><br>

Are you a good player that knows your class and is comfortable with it? Do you like working together with lots of others as a team? Are you intelligent, and don't leave your common sense behind when you press the "Enter World" button? Can and will <b>you</b> make the difference when the water is boiling over?

<br><br>

If you can answer yes to these questions, then Remedy just might be the guild for you. Click <a href=http://pub44.ezboard.com/fremedyfrm1.showMessage?topicID=1137.topic>here</a> to read more about how the recruitment works.

<br><br>

Regardless of what class you are, we are always looking for more powergamers. If you are damn good, and you know it, you still have a chance even if you don't fit into the high, moderate or low demand categories. You'll just have to show us how good you are.

<br><br>

Having said this, let me also say what we are <b>not</b> looking for. We don't want monkeys pushing buttons. We want individuals who can think for themselves and work as part of a team. Don't join for loot, join to play alongside a bunch of friends who share the same love for the game and overcoming new challenges together. Don't join if you spend as much time or more on your twink as on your 'main', we recruit you for the class you are.

<br><br>

Interested? Apply <b>fast!</b> We are going to go back and do every single flag mob soon so you will be able to catch up. Ofcourse, we will only do these flag mobs once each, so you will be expected to be there for every single flag mob, every single day. We can't afford to backtrack even more, as progression is our main game and we are focusing our attention 100% in the elemental planes.

<br><br><br><br><br>

<b>Getting onto what we've killed...</b>

<br><br>

We've basically been in farm mode for a while. Having killed pretty much everything in all the elementals, except the Gods themselves, we've been getting a shitload of <a href=http://www.amm-electronics.net/remedy/blabla/elementalarmor.JPG><b>Elemental Armor</b></a> and absolutely tons of other pretty goddamn good <a href=http://www.amm-electronics.net/remedy/blabla/loots.JPG><b>Loots</b></a>. Actually, it's pouring in. Only complaint is we've gotten like 7 Orb of the Sun's in the last 5 Solusek Ro slayings... How about some variety, please? Here's some pictures of stuff we've killed...<br><br><center><img src=http://www.amm-electronics.net/remedy/blabla/babnoxiz.JPG><img src=http://www.amm-electronics.net/remedy/blabla/criare.JPG><br><img src=http://www.amm-electronics.net/remedy/blabla/elementalmasterpiece.JPG><img src=http://www.amm-electronics.net/remedy/blabla/jaxoliz.JPG><br><img src=http://www.amm-electronics.net/remedy/blabla/mistavatar.JPG><img src=http://www.amm-electronics.net/remedy/blabla/ofossaa.JPG><br><img src=http://www.amm-electronics.net/remedy/blabla/peregrin.JPG><img src=http://www.amm-electronics.net/remedy/blabla/phoenix.JPG><br><img src=http://www.amm-electronics.net/remedy/blabla/pyronis.JPG><img src=http://www.amm-electronics.net/remedy/blabla/tantisala.JPG><br><img src=http://www.amm-electronics.net/remedy/blabla/yozanni.JPG><img src=http://www.amm-electronics.net/remedy/blabla/windavatar.JPG><br><img src=http://www.amm-electronics.net/remedy/blabla/ralloscorpse.JPG></center><br><br>...and way way way way more mobs I didn't bother to screenshot. All in all, it's good times. We found the Guardian of Doomfire up late one night, and decided to give it a shot. Three hours and two bags of runes later this fella spawned<br><br><img src=http://www.amm-electronics.net/remedy/blabla/fennin.JPG><br><br>It was pretty miserable, we were down to about 30 people, at 4 am. The LSD was slowly starting to wear off, but we decided to pull him anyway and give it a shot. Wham bam, thank you maam. Got him to like 90% or something on first shot. We havn't gone back and given him a 2nd try, but I can as good as say right now that his days are counted. I gotta say I really like this script. While it may be alot of clearing, and alot of the same mobs all over again, seeing stuff like this...<br><br><img src=http://www.amm-electronics.net/remedy/blabla/doomfire.JPG><br><br>...really kicks ass. Well, kicked our ass anyway when Jmich decided to pull it all on us. Expect him dead soon.<br><br><br>As a little finish, before getting to the quotes, I would just like to congratulate <b>Badcat</b> and <b>Lasam</b> on getting married. From the pictures I've seen, they had an awesome wedding in Taiwan. We all hope they come back as soon as the jar of Viagra i gave them as a wedding gift is used up.<br><br><br><b>Quotes of the day</b><br><br><img src=http://www.amm-electronics.net/remedy/blabla/dageony.GIF><br><br><img src=http://www.amm-electronics.net/remedy/blabla/eellee.GIF><br><br><img src=http://www.amm-electronics.net/remedy/blabla/hratli.GIF><br><br><img src=http://www.amm-electronics.net/remedy/blabla/jmich.GIF><br><br><img src=http://www.amm-electronics.net/remedy/blabla/karekgogo.GIF><br><br><img src=http://www.amm-electronics.net/remedy/blabla/larcenciel.GIF><br><br><img src=http://www.amm-electronics.net/remedy/blabla/larcenciel2.GIF><br><br><img src=http://www.amm-electronics.net/remedy/blabla/larcenciel3.GIF><br><br><img src=http://www.amm-electronics.net/remedy/blabla/larcenciel4.GIF><br><br><img src=http://www.amm-electronics.net/remedy/blabla/leandred.GIF><br><br><img src=http://www.amm-electronics.net/remedy/blabla/moster.GIF><br><br><img src=http://www.amm-electronics.net/remedy/blabla/nisse.GIF><br><br><img src=http://www.amm-electronics.net/remedy/blabla/rinderwahn.GIF><br><br><img src=http://www.amm-electronics.net/remedy/blabla/rinderwahn2.GIF><br><br><img src=http://www.amm-electronics.net/remedy/blabla/rinderwa